    • LogEntry

      LogEntry​(String callerName, Object result, Map<String,​Object> additionalInfo)
      Parameters:
      callerName - human-readable name (usually in the format ClassName.MethodName) where the LogEntry is logged from
      result - a single string representing the result of the operation that is being logged
      additionalInfo - a map containing any additional information that may help to explain the result, the keys should be variable names and the values should be their values. For convenience, the values are allowed to be any Objects that get converted to Strings in this constructor using: 
      
 additionalInfo

 .stream()
 .collect(Collectors.toMap(
     Map.Entry::getKey,
     entry -> String.valueOf(entry.getValue()))
 );
